  "prompt": "PLAN-GATE PROTOCOL ACTIVE. Real-money urgency: 9 open Coinbase positions remain unprotected at the venue (~$2,700 exposure). The bracket-coverage fix (commit 77d9a5e) sealed Bugs A/B/C in the reconciler/writer chain, but Coinbase REST is rejecting every stop placement. ALEPH-USD's error 'Too many decimals in order price' is the smoking gun -- the venue adapter doesn't quantize to product-level tick_size before submitting.\n\nThe FULL rules + brief are in markdown. Read in this order before planning:\n  1. CLAUDE.md\n  2. docs/STRATEGY/PROTOCOL.md\n  3. docs/STRATEGY/COWORK_ADVISOR_BRIEF.md (Section 2 hazards, especially 2.1 anti-truncation)\n  4. docs/STRATEGY/QUEUED/f-coinbase-tick-size-precision-fix.md (the brief)\n  5. docs/STRATEGY/NEXT_TASK.md (status check)\n  6. app/services/trading/venue/coinbase_spot.py (the file you're modifying)\n  7. tests/test_coinbase_*.py (any existing fixture conventions)\n\nThen follow the brief end to end: write plan.request.md, wait for approval, implement with anti-truncation discipline (Write for files >500 lines), wip-commit per checkpoint, write CC_REPORT, update NEXT_TASK to DONE.\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS:\n  - Coinbase venue adapter ONLY. Do NOT touch reconciler, writer, stop_engine, autotrader, or Robinhood adapter.\n  - Edit-tool truncation discipline. After each modification: wc -l + git diff --stat + python ast.parse.\n  - No magic-fallback values. If product-info fetch fails, raise -- do NOT default to a guessed tick_size.\n  - Coinbase Phase 6 LIVE soak active. The fix is purely additive (quantize before submit). Do NOT disable existing safety gates.\n  - Plan-gate protocol active.",
